\{ $q5->buttons \}

$PAR
True or false:
If \(f \colon {\mathbb{R}} \to \mathbb{R}\) and
\(g \colon {\mathbb{R}} \to \mathbb{R}\) are such that
\(f(0) = g(0) = 0,\) and both are differentiable at \(0,\) then
the composition
\(h := f \circ g\) is differentiable at \(0.\)
$BR
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

